' =============================================================================
' style.puml -- shared PlantUML styling for CYO Adventure architecture diagrams
' -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
' Include from a diagram by adding, just after that diagram's opening line:
'
'     !include style.puml
'
' (use a path relative to the including diagram's location). This file is
' include-only: it declares no diagram of its own and renders nothing directly.
' The SVG generator (tools/generate_diagram_svgs.py) skips any .puml with no
' real diagram-start line, so this file is never rendered on its own.
'
' It codifies the palette and skinparams that the existing top-level diagrams
' currently inline by hand. New diagrams SHOULD include it instead of
' copy-pasting skinparams; see STYLE_GUIDE.md for the full convention set,
' including the domain-to-colour mapping and the traceability-note format.
'
' NOTE: the existing 20 diagrams still inline these values (retrofitting them to
' !include would re-render every SVG for no visual change). Keep any inline
' values in sync with the constants below.
' =============================================================================

' --- Base canvas -------------------------------------------------------------
skinparam defaultFontName "Roboto"
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam roundCorner 8
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #555555
  FontColor #222222
}
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #555555
  FontColor #222222
}

' --- Domain palette (preprocessor colour constants) --------------------------
' Fill colours carry meaning; keep them consistent across diagrams so a reader
' learns the legend once. See STYLE_GUIDE.md for the authoritative mapping.
'
' NOTE: PlantUML rejects a trailing "'" comment on a "!$" line (it swallows the
' comment into the value), so each colour's meaning is documented here, not
' inline. Do not add end-of-line comments to the assignments below.
'
'   kid_blue      Child / PWA surface (container fill)
'   kid_blue_sub  Child / PWA sub-component fill
'   backend_green Backend / guardian surface (container fill)
'   backend_sub   Backend sub-component fill
'   backend_teal  Backend runtime process (e.g. uvicorn app)
'   admin_purple  Admin / global safety operator
'   build_grey    Build output or external / managed system
'   store_amber   Data store (Postgres / Redis / object storage)
!$kid_blue       = "#E3F2FD"
!$kid_blue_sub   = "#DDEEFF"
!$backend_green  = "#E8F5E9"
!$backend_sub    = "#CCEECC"
!$backend_teal   = "#B2DFDB"
!$admin_purple   = "#EDE7F6"
!$build_grey     = "#E0E0E0"
!$store_amber    = "#FFF3E0"

' --- Status stereotypes ------------------------------------------------------
' Use these for elements that are NOT yet shipped so "planned" reads as a
' deliberate mark, not an omission. Verify against code before removing them.
skinparam rectangle<<planned>> {
  BackgroundColor #FCE4EC
  BorderColor #AD1457
  FontColor #880E4F
}
skinparam rectangle<<unverified>> {
  BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
  BorderColor #F57F17
  FontColor #E65100
}
